<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Wu Yi, Indian Counterpart Discuss Trade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Wu Yi, Indian Counterpart Discuss Trade </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Wu Yi on Sino-Indian Cooperation </H4>

<F P=102> OW1706115294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1108 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1706115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New Delhi, June 17 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Minister of 
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Wu Yi said here today 
that economic cooperation between China and India far exceeds 
competition. 
  She made the remark at the luncheon hosted by the 
Confederation of Indian Industry (CII) in her honor when 
answering a question from an Indian journalist. 
  China is trying to build a socialist market economy and 
India's economy is a market one, she said, adding that the 
nature of the market economy is competition. 
  The Chinese minister said that cooperation and competitions 
are inter-dependent and there exists a certain competition 
between the two countries in the international market. 
  "But that is a friendly competition and the cooperation 
between China and India exceeds competition actually," she said. 
  In her speech, Wu Yi elaborated the Chinese Government 
policies on foreign investment and joint ventures and answered 
questions from Indian businessmen present at the luncheon. 
  Today, the Chinese minister also met Indian Minister of 
State 
for Coal A.K. Panja and Indian Minister of State for Petroleum 
and Natural Gas S. Sharma. 
  Both sides discussed matters relating to the further 
development of cooperation between the two countries in the 
areas of coal, steel as well as petroleum and natural gas. 
  Wu Yi will be leaving here this evening for the next and 
last 
leg of her four-Asian-nation visit, Singapore. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

