<F P=100> Near East &amp; South Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Wu Yi, Indian Counterpart Discuss Trade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Wu Yi, Indian Counterpart Discuss Trade </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Indian Business Delegation To Visit </H4>

<F P=102> OW1706131394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1249 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1706131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New Delhi, June 17 (XINHUA) -- An Indian 
businessmen team organized by the Confederation of Indian 
Industries (CII) is leaving tomorrow for China to look for 
business and cooperation opportunities. 
  This was announced by CII President Subodh Bhargava today at 
the luncheon hosted by CII in honour of visiting Chinese 
Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Trade Wu Yi. 
  The CII mission will visit several places in China during 
the 
period from June 20 to June 24, Bhargava said. 
  "The main objective of the mission is to look at the 
possibilities of developing trade, business and investment 
cooperation between the two countries," the CII president said. 
  He expressed the hope that the CII will send another team to 
China later in the year and to meet the industrialists in the 
interior provinces of China. 
  Bhargava said that he was very happy at the considerable 
improvement of bilateral trade between India and China last year. 
  "With economic and trade liberalization in India and China 
opening its market to the world and also to each other, CII will 
play an effective and catalytic role enabling members of Indian 
and Chinese industry to take the advantages of the open-door 
policy of the two governments," he said. 
  The CII president noted that Chinese overseas trade is of 
the 
order of nearly 200 billion U.S. dollars per year while the 
India- China trade stood at less than 700 million U.S. dollars 
last year. 
  "Both have a developing economy and therefore the potential 
for mutual beneficial business can well understood by any 
businessmen," he said. 

</TEXT>

