<H3> <TI>   Minister Wu Yi, Indian Counterpart Discuss Trade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Wu Yi, Indian Counterpart Discuss Trade </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sino-Indian Meeting Set for 27-28 Jun </H4>

<F P=102> OW1806064494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0631 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1806064494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New Delhi, June 18 (XINHUA) -- A Sino-Indian 
conference on the five principles of peaceful coexistence will 
be held on June 27 to 28. 
  The five principles of peaceful coexistence in the 
contemporary world first formulated by China and India in 1954 
would be the main theme of the conference, officials here said 
today. 
  It is learned that Indian Prime Minister Narasimha Rao would 
inaugurate the conference and eminent academics, diplomats and 
intellectuals from the two countries would attend the conference. 
  The main theme would be discussed in three sessions-- 
international relations and diplomacy, world trade and economic 
systems in connection with challenges and opportunities, and 
lasting peace and security issues. 

</TEXT>

