<H3> <TI>   CPC Official Wei Jianxing Meets Israeli Communists </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CPC Official Wei Jianxing Meets Israeli Communists </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1906120194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1143 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1906120194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 19 (XINHUA) -- Wei Jianxing, member 
of the Political Bureau and the Secretariat of the Central 
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), met with and 
feted a delegation from the Communist Party of Israel (CPI) here 
this evening. 
  On behalf of General Secretary of the CPC Central Committee 
Jiang Zemin, Wei extended a welcome to the delegation headed by 
CPI General Secretary Muhamed Naffa, saying that the relations 
between CPC and CPI have been developing well since the two 
parties resumed their ties in 1987. 
  Wei briefed the visitors on the current political and 
economic situation in China. He said that the major reform 
measures which China has taken since the beginning of this year 
have been going smoothly and produced better results than 
expected. 
  He said China, enjoying a good political and economic 
situation, must handle well the relations between reform, 
development and stability. 
  The CPI delegation arrived here yesterday on a visit to 
China 
at the invitation of the CPC. 

</TEXT>

