<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Secretary Jiang Zemin Inspects Zhuhai Enterprises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Secretary Jiang Zemin Inspects Zhuhai Enterprises </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Jiang Visits Factory Fire Victims </H4>

<F P=102> HK2006043594 Hong Kong WEN WEI PO in Chinese 20 Jun 94 p a2 </F>
<F P=103> HK2006043594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong WEN WEI PO </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report: "Jiang Zemin, Qian Qichen Inspect Zhuhai"] </F>
  [Text] Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC and 
president of the PRC, inspected Zhuhai, Guangdong, 17-19 June. 
On 18 June, he came to the Zhuhai People's Hospital to visit 
and extend regards to workers who were injured when the former 
Zhuhai Shanyuxin textile factory collapsed after catching fire, 
kindly telling them to concentrate on receiving treatment; the 
workers were greatly moved. After staying in the wards on the 
first and third floors for more than 10 minutes, Jiang left in a 
car. According to an injured worker in a ward, President Jiang 
asked each patient the following questions: Where are you 
injured? Where do you live? Do you have any relatives in 
Zhuhai? He hoped they would concentrate on receiving medical 
treatment and wished they would recover soon. The injured 
workers were very glad at the visit by a state leader. 
  In the afternoon of the same day, Qian Qichen, vice premier 
and foreign minister, came to the site where the textile factory 
had collapsed so as to gain an understanding of the situation. 
He expressed appreciation for the Zhuhai Government's efforts 
to rescue the victims. 
  It has been proved that 24 people died as a result of the 
accident. The relatives of the dead have begun to identify the 
remains. Over 50 percent of the accident site has been cleaned 
up. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

