<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiang Phones Guangxi Party Secretary on Floods </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jiang Phones Guangxi Party Secretary on Floods </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1906133594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1304 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1906133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nanning, June 19 (XINHUA) -- Jiang Zemin, general 
secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central 
Committee, telephoned Zhao Fulin, secretary of the CPC committee 
of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, Saturday [18 June] 
evening to express his solicitude for the people in the flooded 
area of the region. 
  Jiang asked about the flood situation, the local people's 
efforts to fight the disaster, and the central and local 
governments' relief efforts. He expressed his sympathy and 
solicitude for the people of various nationalities in Guangxi 
and for the cadres, common people, and officers and men of the 
People's Liberation Army, armed police force and public security 
force who are combating the flood. 
  After hearing Zhao's report, Jiang noted that the Xijiang 
River in Guangxi is still at a flood peak and the water level 
remains high. "Even when the flood peak passes," he said, 
"efforts should be made to help the local people to tide over 
the disaster. Party committees and governments at all levels in 
the region should concentrate during the current period on the 
work of combating the flood and delivering disaster relief." 
  He said the party, government and people should spare no 
efforts in the fight against the floods and in safeguarding the 
people's lives and property. Leaders at all levels should go to 
the frontline of the battle against the flood, keep abreast of 
the flood situation, organize the masses to overcome 
difficulties and reduce losses and make adequate arrangements 
for their livelihood. 
  Leaders of the Guangxi regional party committee and 
government have held a meeting to discuss how to carry out 
General Secretary Jiang's instructions to mobilize all the 
forces of the party, government and people to overcome the 
disaster. 

</TEXT>

