<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chen Junsheng Warns To Prepare for `Big Floods' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chen Junsheng Warns To Prepare for `Big Floods' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1806171194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1554 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1806171194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 18 (XINHUA) -- State Councilor Chen 
Junsheng today called on China's flood-fighting forces to be 
ready for any big floods that may appear. 
  Presiding over a conference at the State Flood Control and 
Drought Relief Headquarters, which he heads, Chen also urged 
authorities to do a good job in flood relief in Guangdong and 
Guangxi, where major floods have struck and may worsen. 
  Chen was briefed about the flood situations at the 
conference 
by the headquarters, the Ministries of Water Resources and 
Construction and the National Meteorological Bureau. 
  As a result of sustained heavy rainfalls, record water 
levels 
have been reported on the Xijiang River in the Pearl River 
Valley in south China and the Xiangjiang River in central Hunan, 
causing major economic damage and loss of a few lives. 
  Reports from Hunan Province said that 40 counties and 5.3 
million people there have been affected by floods. A total of 
400,000 ha [hectares] of crops were afflicted. 
  Chen warned that special attention has to be paid to the 
Pearl River Delta, where a fast-growing economy may suffer huge 
losses should floods hit. 
  The conference decided to send working groups to Guangdong 
and Guangxi. The groups will be composed of officials from the 
Ministries of Water Resources, Construction and Civil Affairs, 
and the State Economic and Trade Commission, as well as from the 
headquarters of the General Staff of the People's Liberation 
Army, to help coordinate local flood control efforts. 

</TEXT>

