<F P=102>   OW2006085494 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0637 
GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2006085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, June 19 (XINHUA) -- Yi Meihou, renowned 
patriotic Overseas Chinese leader, vice president of the 
All-China Federation of Returned Overseas Chinese, and former 
vice chairman of the Guangdong Provincial People's Congress 
Standing Committee, died of sickness on 29 May at the age of 86. 
A ceremony to pay last respects to Yi Meihou's remains was held 
in Guangzhou on 18 June. 
  Sending cables, letters, or wreaths to express condolences 
were Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Liu Huaqing, Tian Jiyun, Li 
Lanqing, Li Tieying, Yang Baibing, Qian Qichen, Xie Fei, Yang 
Shangkun, Lei Jieqiong, Wu Jieping, Wang Zhaoguo, Henry Ying 
Tung Fok [Huo Yingdong], and Ma Man-kei. 
  Attending the ceremony were a few hundred people including 
Ye 
Xuanping, vice chairman of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference's National Committee, and celebrities 
from relevant departments of the central authorities, Guangdong 
Province, Hong Kong, Macao, and abroad. 

</TEXT>

