<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Hospital Announces Stomach Cancer Therapy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shanghai Hospital Announces Stomach Cancer Therapy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2006080894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0721 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2006080894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, June 20 (XINHUA) -- Adding iodized oil to 
an arterial infusion of chemicals is effective in treating 
late-stage gastric carcinoma (cancer of the stomach), according 
to physicians at the Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to the 
Shanghai Medical Sciences University. 
  The morbidity rate of stomach cancer is among the highest of 
all types of cancer. Advanced-stage stomach tumors cannot be 
removed surgically, and chemotherapy is the only way to ease 
pain. 
  Since the early 1980s hospitals all over the world have 
administered infusions of chemicals through arteries. But under 
such treatment only about 25 percent of the victims can live one 
year. 
  Iodized oil is a kind of embolism agent. When it is infused 
into the stomach artery it can selectively deposit itself into 
and around the small blood vessels of the tumor, and cut the 
blood supply to it. Thus, it kills or inhibits the expansion of 
cancer cells. However, it will not reduce the growth of healthy 
cells. 
  According to Wang Xiaolin, one of the staff physicians at 
the 
hospital, the chemicals carried by the iodized oil can stay on 
permanently to kill tumor cells, and hopefully cure the cancer. 
  Experts have appraised the therapy as a safe, simple and 
effective one. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-26195 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi118_l_94004" </HT>


