<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Addresses Postal, Telecommunications Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Addresses Postal, Telecommunications Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2006062994 Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2006062994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Provincial News Hookup" program] </F>
  [Text] A national postal and telecommunications conference 
opened in Hangzhou today. Minister of Posts and 
Telecommunications Wu Jichuan and Vice Governor Zhang Qimei of 
Zhejiang attended and spoke at the conference. 
  The conferees called for improving the organizational 
planning and structural readjustment of first-class postal trunk 
networks this year, by rationalizing the postal transportation 
system, actively setting up independent and exclusive air postal 
routes, ensuring a good job in the readjustment and distribution 
of motor vehicle postal transportation networks, and 
accelerating the completion of auxiliary equipment for 
heavy-duty trucks and other supplementary facilities in a bid to 
raise the postal transportation capacity. 
  They said: During the Ninth Five-Year Plan period, there 
will be 20 postal transport planes, 36,000 km air trunk postal 
routes operated by the ministry, 9,700 motor vehicles for trunk 
postal transportation, and 280,000 km of motor vehicle trunk 
postal routes operated by the ministry, thereby gradually 
setting up a relatively independent postal transport system 
which comprehensively utilizes planes, motor vehicles, trains, 
and ships and which combines routes operated by the ministry 
with those operated by other departments consigned by the 
ministry. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

