<F P=102>   OW1806093494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0851 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1806093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, June 18 (XINHUA) -- China's Huaneng 
International Power Development Corporation will be granted ADR 
(American Drawing Rights) to list stocks on the New York Stock 
Exchange from June 23. 
  According to the Shanghai Stock Exchange, this will be the 
first of China's second batch of five state-owned enterprises to 
be listed worldwide. 
  The other four are China Eastern Airlines, China Southern 
Airlines, the Shandong Huaneng Enterprise Group and the Tianjin 
Steel Tube Plant. 
  "This indicates that China's reform of its joint stock 
system 
is bringing this sector into line with the international 
standards and that its state-owned enterprises are arousing 
greater interest of business people overseas," an exchange 
official said. 
  The first batch of three Chinese state-owned enterprises 
listed on the New York Stock Exchange are operating smoothly. 

