Daily Report 
<DATE1>  18 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry of Agriculture Expects `Good Summer Harvest' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry of Agriculture Expects `Good Summer Harvest' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1906014494 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0330 GMT 
18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1906014494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 18 (CNS) -- According to the Ministry 
of Agriculture, though the area under cultivation of summer 
grain crops this year in the country is seven million mu less 
than that of last year, China is still expected to have a good 
summer harvest this year. 
  The area cultivated for rape seeds this year is about 84.2 
million mu of land in the country, 7.7 million mu more than that 
of last year. The actual harvesting area is estimated to be 
around 80 million mu, 5 million mu more than that of last year. 
Its gross output is predicted to have a remarkable increase 
this summer. 
  The production of summer grain crop this year met some 
difficulties. First, owing to the restructuring of crop 
planting, this summer's grain-crops-growing area dropped. 
Second, because of the adjustment of exchange rate of renminbi 
and price rise, prices for the main agricultural production 
materials increased greatly. Third, the weather in early days in 
such crops' growing period was not so good with the accumulated 
temperature in this period being 200 to 300 degrees centigrade 
less than that in past years. 
  Thanks to the strengthening of field management and good 
weather in later days, a good harvest of such crops including 
wheat is guaranteed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

