<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Reports Carter's 2nd Meeting With Kim Il-song </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Reports Carter's 2nd Meeting With Kim Il-song </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706141594 Beijing XINHUA in English 1340 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1706141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 17 (XINHUA) -- The President of the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) Kim Il-song met 
with former U.S. President Jimmy Carter and his wife a second 
time at noon here today. 
  Kim's wife Kim Song-ae also joined the meeting this time, 
according to local press reports, which said Kim and Carter had 
sincere talks over issues of common concern. No other details 
were disclosed. 
  Carter is due to cross the demarcation line at Panmunjom on 
Saturday [18 June] on his way back to Seoul, where he is 
expected to brief South Korean President Kim Yong-sam on the 
results of his talks with Kim Il-song. 
  Carter's visit to DPRK is aimed at facilitating exchanges of 
views on the nuclear issue among the United States, South Korea 
and the DPRK. He had talks with South Korean leaders earlier 
this week before arriving in Pyongyang on Wednesday. 
  Kim Il-song had his first meeting with carter on Thursday 
and 
they talked in a cordial atmosphere, according to local press 
reports. 

</TEXT>

