<H3> <TI>   Vice Premier Li Lanqing Meets U.S. Bankers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vice Premier Li Lanqing Meets U.S. Bankers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1806084094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0829 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1806084094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 18 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier 
Li Lanqing met with George Vojta, vice-chairman of the U.S. 
Bankers Trust Company, and his party here today. 
  On June 15, the company donated 5 million renminbi yuan 
(some 
600,000 U.S. dollars) to the "Hope Project" for the building of 
primary schools in China's relatively economic backward areas. 
  Li expressed gratitude for the donation. China is willing to 
further expand its cooperation with the company in financial and 
investment spheres as well as in training of qualified 
personnel, he said. 
  Vojta voiced his pleasure with his company's progress in 
business operation in China, and wished the country still 
greater achievements in its reform and opening-up process. 

</TEXT>

