<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cambodian Government Expels Khmer Rouge From Capital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cambodian Government Expels Khmer Rouge From Capital </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706145294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1424 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1706145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh, June 17 (XINHUA) -- The Cambodian 
Government decided today to expel the representative office of 
the Khmer Rouge from the capital Phnom Penh. 
  Meanwhile, government forces have begun bombing the western 
town of Pailin heralding another major assault on the Khmer 
Rouge stronghold, according to Khmer Rouge sources tonight. 
  Cambodian television has broadcast messages from the 
co-ministers of interior affairs Sar Kheng and You Kockry who 
said that the people of Phnom Penh are "indignant" over the 
failure of the round-table meeting on June 15-16, and indicated 
they would retaliate against the representative office. 
  The government has warned it can no longer guarantee the 
safety of the Khmer Rouge staff in Phnom Penh and recommended 
them to leave before June 19. 
  But it will ensure their safety to the airport if they 
advise 
a departure timetable at least one day before leaving. 
  However, the government stressed that if any staff miss the 
deadline, anything could happen and it will not protect them if 
they are attacked. 
  A spokesman also read out a strongly-worded statement on 
television tonight, denouncing the Khmer Rouge for rejecting a 
ceasefire proposal by King Sihanouk and thus rejecting the will 
of the nation and the people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

