<F P=100> PRC MEDIA ON TAIWAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   ARATS Suggests Further Negotiations With SEF </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ARATS Suggests Further Negotiations With SEF </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1806131194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1302 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1806131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 18 (XINHUA) -- The Association for 
Relations Across the Taiwan Straits (ARATS) of the mainland 
suggested in a letter to the Taiwan-based Straits Exchange 
Foundation (SEF) Friday [17 June] to hold further talks between 
the two organizations soon. 
  The letter said that ARATS hopes the negotiations will help 
resolve disputes at an early date and help them to finalize 
three other agreements, including one involving the repatriation 
of people who entered the other side through illegal means. 
  The fourth business-like negotiations, which were held 
earlier this year, did not reach expected results due to various 
factors, said the letter. 
  Tang Shubei, executive vice-chairman of ARATS, said in a 
separate letter to Chiao Jen Ho [Jiao Renhe], vice-chairman of 
SEF, that he hopes both Jiao and he would make joint efforts to 
help promote cooperation between the two organizations and 
improve relations across the Taiwan Straits. 
  The letter said that in accordance with agreements reached 
earlier, the time to hold the bi-annual meeting between 
officials in charge of the two organizations and the quarterly 
meeting between officials at the deputy secretary general level 
will come soon. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

