<H3> <TI>   State Councillor Luo Gan Winds Up Visit to Cyprus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Councillor Luo Gan Winds Up Visit to Cyprus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1906075594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0711 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1906075594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Larnaca, Cyprus, June 19 (XINHUA) -- Luo Gan, state 
councillor and secretary general of China's State Council, and 
his delegation left here for Tunisia today winding up a 
three-day good will visit to this Mediterranean island country. 
  During his stay in Cyprus, Luo and his party met Cyprus 
President Glavcos Kliridhis and President of the House of 
Representatives Alexis Galanos [name as received]. Both sides 
expressed satisfaction over the smooth development of good 
relations between the two countries. 
  The delegation also held talks with Cyprus Acting Foreign 
Minister, Interior Minister Konstandinos Mikhailidhis, during 
which bilateral relations, economic and trade cooperation as 
well as the cyprus issue were discussed. 
  Cyprus is the delegations' first leg in their tour in the 
region, which will also take them to Tunisia and Libya. 

</TEXT>

