<H3> <TI>   General Li Jiulong Leads Delegation To Burma, Laos </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    General Li Jiulong Leads Delegation To Burma, Laos </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrives in Burma </H4>

<F P=102> OW2206085094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0825 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yangon, [Rangoon] June 22 (XINHUA) -- A Chinese 
military delegation, led by General Li Jiulong, commander of the 
Chengdu Military Region of the People's Liberation Army, arrived 
here today to begin one-week friendly visit to Myanmar [Burma]. 
  The delegation was met by Myanmar Chief of Staff (Army) and 
Commander of No. 1 Bureau of Special Operations 
Lieutenant-General, Tin Oo and other high officers, Chinese 
Ambassador to Myanmar Liang Feng and Chinese military attache 
Senior Colonel Wu Huachang at Yangon airport. 
  At the invitation of the Myanmar Ministry of Defense, the 
Chinese delegation came to Myanmar for a friendly visit. 

</TEXT>

