<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   My Father Deng Xiaoping Published in Thai </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    My Father Deng Xiaoping Published in Thai </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2206091694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0853 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2206091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bangkok, June 22 (XINHUA) -- A Thai version of Deng 
Xiaoping biography written by his daughter, Deng Rong, has been 
published in Thailand. 
  The book, My Father Deng Xiaoping tells about the 
life and struggle of the great man and great events and changes 
of China since early this century. 
  Published by the Managers' Daily, the Thai version of the 
book will provide a good channel for Thai-speaking readers to 
get to know more about Deng Xiaoping and contemporary China. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

