<H3> <TI>   Citizens, XINHUA Branch Donate to Flood Victims </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Citizens, XINHUA Branch Donate to Flood Victims </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2106163494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1516 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2106163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, June 21 (XINHUA) -- The XINHUA NEWS 
AGENCY Hong Kong [HK] branch today donated a total of 425,980 HK 
dollars (about 54,613 U.S. dollars) to help relieve the 
devastating floods in six south China provinces and regions. 
  The branch also set up a special flood relief office and 
re-opened a flood relief account in Bank of China Hong Kong 
branch to receive donations from Hong Kong residents and 
organizations. 
  Up to now, Hong Kong residents and organizations, together 
with major Chinese (mainland) institutions in the territory, 
have donated about 30 million HK dollars (about 3.846 million 
U.S. dollars) for the flood-hit areas. 
  Since early June, the provinces and regions of Guangdong, 
Guangxi, Hunan, Jiangxi, Zhejiang and Fujian have suffered from 
severe floods which caused 438 people dead and 480,000-plus 
houses down with an estimated economic loss of 17 billion 
renminbi yuan (about 1.954 billion U.S. dollars). 

</TEXT>

